{"version":3,"term":{"cols":80,"rows":24},"timestamp":1781461344,"command":"bash docs/recording/demo-ceos.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.010, "o", "\u001b[3J\u001b[H\u001b[2J"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1mrocannon\u001b[0m  your Ansible collections as typed MCP tools\r\nClaude Haiku driving a 2-node Arista cEOS fabric, in natural language\r\n\r\n"]
[3.595, "o", "connecting to the Rocannon MCP server...\r\n"]
[5.856, "o", "\r\nUSER: What model and EOS software version is ceos1 running?\r\n"]
[4.602, "o", "  \u001b[33m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1marista_eos_eos_facts\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mtarget=ceos1\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.050, "o", "    \u001b[2m↳ status=successful  changed=False\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.230, "o", "  \u001b[36mclaude\u001b[0m  Based on the facts gathered from **ceos1**:\r\n\r\n- **Model**: cEOSLab (Arista CloudEOS Lab)\r\n- **EOS Software Version**: 4.36.0.1F-47425148.43601F (engineering build)\r\n\r\nThis is a containerized Arista EOS lab instance running version 4.36.\r\n"]
[0.038, "o", "\r\nUSER: What is ceos1 directly connected to? Look at its LLDP neighbors.\r\n"]
[2.656, "o", "  \u001b[33m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1marista_eos_eos_command\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mtarget=ceos1  commands=[\"show lldp neighbors\"]\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.914, "o", "    \u001b[2m↳ status=successful  changed=False\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.958, "o", "  \u001b[36mclaude\u001b[0m  Based on the LLDP neighbors output, **ceos1 is directly connected to ceos2**:\r\n\r\n- **ceos1 Port**: Ethernet1 (Et1)\r\n- **Connected to**: ceos2\r\n- **ceos2 Port**: Ethernet1\r\n\r\nThis is a simple point-to-point connection between the two devices, established 35 minutes ago.\r\n"]
[0.050, "o", "\r\nUSER: Set the login banner on ceos1 to exactly 'Managed by Rocannon' and tell me whether it changed anything.\r\n"]
[2.465, "o", "  \u001b[33m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1marista_eos_eos_banner\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mtarget=ceos1  banner=login  text=Managed by Rocannon\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.340, "o", "    \u001b[2m↳ status=successful  changed=True\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.380, "o", "  \u001b[36mclaude\u001b[0m  ✅ **Yes, it changed something.** \r\n\r\nThe login banner on ceos1 has been successfully set to exactly `Managed by Rocannon`. The configuration change was applied with the following commands:\r\n- `banner login`\r\n- `Managed by Rocannon`\r\n- `EOF`\r\n\r\nThe `changed: true` status confirms that the device configuration was modified.\r\n"]
[0.298, "o", "\u001b[?25h"]
[1.105, "x", "0"]
